detaileddescription.para:
When an infinity appears in the abstract evaluation the program should return \bCSL_INF. \bCSL_INF is treated like a Variable. It is simply here to inform the user that *something bad happened** in the expr. Bug
Will not work for many cases, in particular log(0)!=\bCSL_INF. Not yet implemented.

briefdescription.para: Constant that is useful in return of non-defined calculations as for example Commutator(): [A,B] returns CSL_UNDEF when it is not defined (more than AB-BA). It allows the program to avoid circular calculations and seg fault.
